<catsoop-section>Instructions</catsoop-section>

1. First set gears on the given flat surface such that 7-6-5 spoked gears are arranged left to right.

2. Now set letters of tooth such that 7 spoked gear gets letter D, 6 spoked gear gets the letter O, 5 spoked gear gets the letter G at marked lines. This is **7-6-5 DOG**.

3. Now write a message on a paper. Let's say "Centre for creativity" and we will encrypt these words on our gear enigma.

4. First divide the given message in 4-4 words. So our words will be 'CENT REFO RCRE ATIV ITY'. If the message is not equally divided in 4 words then add a sequence of characters to the end of the last block to fill it complete. So our message will be **CENT REFO RCRE ATIV ITYZ** (as Z comes after Y in alphabets).

5. First rotate 5 spoked gear so that its tooth meeting at the marked line gets the letter C.

6. Now see the resultant tooth at the marked line of 7 spoked gear — that is **H**.

7. Encrypt another letter of our message 'E'. This time we will see the encrypted letter on 6 spoked gear and we will get the letter **P**.

8. Thus continue this process by encrypting letters on 7 spoked gear and 6 spoked gear alternatively.

9. So we will get **HPWA SPEH …**

10. To decrypt this message, first use the 7 spoked gear's tooth's letter at marked line and see which letter we will get on 5 spoked gear's tooth at marked line. Then use 6 spoked gear's letter. Do this process alternatively with 7 and 6 spoked gears. And see the decrypted message.

Have you decrypted the message? Ahey! You are the decoder!

<catsoop-section>What's Happening</catsoop-section>

Here we have three gears with 26 teeth. The 5 spoked gear's teeth contain capital alphabets in clockwise direction while 7 spoked gear's teeth contain alphabets in anticlockwise direction. The middle one (6 spoked gear) teeth contain alphabets alternatively — that is BACEDFHG… in clockwise direction.

As we rotate 5 spoked gear clockwise, the middle one (6 spoked gear) rotates anticlockwise. And hence the 7 spoked gear will rotate clockwise and vice versa.

As we set our gear at keyword **7-6-5 DOG**, alphabets are set in this way as shown in the image. Also, as we divide our message in 4-4 blocks, our encrypted message is on 7-6-7-6 spoked gear pattern. So it becomes easier to decrypt our message.

